narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The year-long project is worth it.
Need to take it for the major requirements, but make sure to give it your 100% to feel fully satisfied with your end product.
It is definitely as much work as a regular class but you have to make sure you do it on your own. It is easy to procrastinate since there are only a few hard deadlines.

The course was necessary for completion of my HSHM senior thesis. It was not a course that met in a classroom with a professor, but rather, more of an independent study sort of course. I arranged to meet with my adviser on an as-per-necessary basis.
